## Palindrome Linked List - to find if a linked list is a palindrome

1. find the middle node of the list (fast and slow pointer)
2. disconnect first half and second half of linked list
3. reverse the linked list from the middle node (end node of linked list now becomes the middle node)
4. iteratively compare node values while both halves exist
5. if either of the heads are None (odd palindrome) or both heads are None (even palindrome) , it is a pallindrome

class Solution:
    def isPalindrome(self, head):
        slow,fast=head,head.next
        while fast and fast.next:
            slow=slow.next
            fast=fast.next.next
        mid=slow.next
        slow.next=None
        prev,cur=None,mid
        while cur:
            nxt=cur.next
            cur.next=prev
            prev=cur
            cur=nxt
        head1,head2=head,prev
        while head1 and head2:
            if head1.data!=head2.data: return False
            head1=head1.next
            head2=head2.next
        return True
